# MACOS
brew install neovim ripgrep fd fzf gcc
rm -rf ~/.config/nvim ~/.local/share/nvim ~/.local/state/nvim ~/.cache/nvim


#LINUX
# download image from https://packages.ubuntu.com/search?keywords=neovim
chmod u+x nvim-linux-x86_64.appimage
sudo mv nvim-linux-x86_64.appimage /usr/local/bin/nvim
sudo apt update
sudo apt install ripgrep fd-find fzf gcc make unzip git -y
rm -rf ~/.config/nvim ~/.local/share/nvim ~/.local/state/nvim ~/.cache/nvim


# LazyVim
git clone https://github.com/LazyVim/starter ~/.config/nvim
rm -rf ~/.config/nvim/.git



# to start
nvim


:LazyExtras
x to package install - go to the line and x again - when exit and reenter it will auto install


# to use
===============================================================================
                       LAZYVIM PERSONAL CHEAT SHEET
===============================================================================
Note: The <leader> key is mapped to the [ Spacebar ] by default.

[ PROJECT EXPLORER & FOLDER VIEW ]
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Space + e       - Open or Close the folder view panel
j / k           - Move cursor down or up the folder list
Enter           - Open highlighted file OR expand/collapse a directory folder
a               - Create a new file (add a trailing '/' for a new folder)
r               - Rename a file or folder
d               - Delete a file or folder (requires prompt confirmation)
.               - Toggle visibility of hidden files (dotfiles like .env)
q               - Close the folder view panel instantly

[ TAB & BUFFER MANAGEMENT ]
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Shift + l       - Switch to the next tab on the RIGHT
Shift + h       - Switch to the next tab on the LEFT
Space + b + d   - Close current tab (Buffer Delete)
Space + [1-9]   - Jump directly to a tab by its sequence number
Space + f + b   - Open an interactive list to fuzzy-search open tabs

[ AUTOCOMPLETE & CODE PROMPTS ]
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Ctrl + n        - Scroll DOWN the popup completion dropdown menu
Ctrl + p        - Scroll UP the popup completion dropdown menu
Enter           - Accept / Confirm the highlighted selection
Ctrl + y        - Alternative shortcut to accept / confirm selection
Right Arrow     - Accept inline gray AI "Ghost Text" predictions

[ RUNNING CODE & EMBEDDED TERMINALS ]
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Ctrl + /        - Toggle the floating terminal over your code
Ctrl + -        - Alternative shortcut to toggle the floating terminal
Ctrl + \ then   - Escape active terminal mode back to normal Vim mode
Ctrl + n          (Allows you to scroll up terminal text using j/k)
:vsplit         - Split your layout screen vertically
:terminal       - Launch a terminal inside your current active window split
:! <command>    - Run a quick, one-off background command (e.g., :! cargo run)

[ FINDING FILES & CODE (TELESCOPE) ]
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Space + f + f   - Fuzzy-search for ANY file name in your current project
Space + s + g   - Live Grep (Search exact text strings inside every single file)

===============================================================================
